Sec. 122.301. MANUFACTURE. (a) Except as provided by
Subsection (b), a state agency may not prohibit a person who
manufactures a product regulated by the agency, other than an article
regulated under Chapter 431, Health and Safety Code, from applying
for or obtaining a permit or other authorization to manufacture the
product solely on the basis that the person intends to manufacture
the product as a nonconsumable hemp product.
(b) A state agency may not authorize a person to manufacture a
product containing hemp for smoking, as defined by Section 443.001,
Health and Safety Code.
Added by Acts 2019, 86th Leg., R.S., Ch. 764 (H.B. 1325), Sec. 2, eff.
June 10, 2019.

